inisters%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20Rajnath%20Singh%20and%20Nitish%20Gadkari%20between%20September%202%20and%205%20from%20five%20corners%20of%20the%20state%2C%20the%20yatras%20are%20evoking%20memories%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20heydays%2C%20when%20he%20crisscrossed%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20as%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20super%20boss%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20pitiable%20appears%20the%20plight%20of%20Chouhan%20that%20for%20issuing%20a%20report%20card%20on%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20performance%20over%20the%20last%2018%20years%2C%20Shah%20rushed%20down%20to%20Bhopal%20on%20August%2021.%20The%20longest%20serving%20chief%20minister%20looked%20on%20as%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20sang%20paeans%20of%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csuccess%E2%80%9D%20in%20removing%20the%20%E2%80%98Bimaru%E2%80%99%20(laggard)%20tag%20from%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20along%20with%20fulsome%20praise%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20performance%20came%20a%20shocker%20for%20him%20from%20Shah%2C%20when%20latter%20sidestepped%20questions%20on%20whether%20the%20incumbent%20chief%20minister%2C%20Chouhan%2C%20will%20continue%20in%20the%20post%20if%20the%20BJP%20is%20voted%20to%20power%20again.%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20party%20will%20decide%20on%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20post%20only%20after%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remarks%20came%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20party%20has%20begun%20campaigning%20for%20the%20polls%2C%20expected%20to%20be%20held%20in%20November%2C%20without%20naming%20a%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20BJP%20does%20not%20traditionally%20names%20its%20chief%20ministerial%20face%20before%20the%20elections%20in%20states%20where%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20the%20opposition.%20The%20states%20where%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20power%2C%20the%20incumbent%20chief%20minister%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20front-runner%20for%20the%20post%20if%20the%20party%20retains%20power.%20However%2C%20senior%20party%20functionaries%20said%20that%20a%20final%20call%20on%20who%20will%20be%20the%20chief%20minister%20is%20taken%20by%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20board%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20highest%20decision%20taking%20body%2C%20after%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChouhan%E2%80%99s%20position%20has%20become%20akin%20to%20S.R.%20Bommai%E2%80%99s%2C%20after%20whose%20term%20as%20Karnataka%20chief%20minister%20the%20BJP%20suffered%20a%20crushing%20defeat%20in%20the%20assembly%20election%20in%20May%20this%20year.%20He%20too%20was%20not%20projected%20as%20chief%20minister.%20Like%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20BJP%20high%20command%20is%20pinning%20its%20hope%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20in%20MP%20and%2C%20accordingly%2C%20devising%20strategies%20to%20keep%20more%20focus%20on%20national%20rather%20than%20state%20issues.%20In%20their%20speeches%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20Union%20cabinet%20ministers%2C%20particularly%20Shah%2C%20laid%20greater%20emphasis%20on%20how%20the%20country%20is%20poised%20to%20become%20a%20%E2%80%98Vishwaguru%E2%80%99%20under%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20On%20state%20subjects%2C%20their%20target%20has%20been%20the%20alleged%20corruption%20during%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%2015-month%20government.%20The%20BJP%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20performance%20scarcely%20found%20mention%20in%20their%20speeches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20central%20leadership%20is%20in%20no%20mood%20to%20project%20the%20incumbent%20chief%20minister%20in%20the%20election%20had%20become%20apparent%20when%20BJP%20president%20J.P.%20Nadda%20on%20July%208%20appointed%20Union%20ministers%20Bhupendra%20Yadav%20as%20the%20state%20election%20in-charge%20and%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20as%20the%20co-in-charge%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20A%20week%20later%2C%20on%20July%2015%2C%20the%20party%20appointed%20Union%20minister%20Narendra%20Singh%20Tomar%20as%20convener%20of%20its%20election%20management%20committee%20for%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20assembly%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETomar%2C%20who%20has%20been%20president%20of%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20unit%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20is%20considered%20a%20low-profile%20leader%20who%20enjoys%20cordial%20relations%20with%20various%20regional%20satraps.%20He%20is%20a%20lawmaker%20from%20Morena%20in%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20region%2C%20where%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20improve%20its%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20Union%20ministers%E2%80%99%20active%20supervision%20in%20various%20capacities%20and%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20close%20monitoring%20of%20the%20election%20preparations%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20has%20rendered%20the%20state%20leadership%E2%80%99s%20power%20strikingly%20weakened.%20It%20became%20obvious%20when%20the%20party%20on%20August%2023%20released%20its%20list%20of%2039%20candidates%20for%20the%20seats%20it%20had%20lost%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Madhya%20Pradesh%3A%20In%20Quest%20for%20Power%2C%20Is%20Congress%20Ready%20to%20Compromise%20on%20Secularism%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmadhya-pradesh-in-quest-for-power-is-congress-ready-to-compromise-on-secularism%5C%22%3EMadhya%20Pradesh%3A%20In%20Quest%20for%20Power%2C%20Is%20Congress%20Ready%20to%20Compromise%20on%20Secularism%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20names%20were%20decided%20at%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Election%20Committee%20(CEC)%20meeting%2C%20chaired%20by%20Nadda%20and%20attended%20by%20Modi%20as%20well%20as%20Union%20ministers%20Rajnath%20Singh%20and%20Shah%2C%20among%20other%20senior%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20candidate%20selection%20was%20said%20to%20be%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20the%20central%20leadership.%20Several%20surprising%20names%20figured%20in%20the%20list%2C%20triggering%20protests%20and%20demonstrations%20against%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20of%20them.%20The%20chief%20minister%2C%20who%20is%20not%20a%20member%20of%20the%20CEC%2C%20had%20little%2C%20if%20any%2C%20say%20in%20the%20selection%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParty%20insiders%20say%20several%20candidates%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20liking%20missed%20the%20bus%20in%20the%20list.%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%20loyalist%20and%20former%20MLA%20Ranveer%20Jatav%20too%20has%20been%20denied%20a%20ticket%20from%20the%20Gohad%20assembly%20seat.%20Jatav%20was%20one%20of%20the%20Congress%20MLAs%20who%20switched%20to%20the%20BJP%20to%20support%20Scindia%20in%20March%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20central%20leadership%20being%20firm%20on%20not%20changing%20any%20names%20on%20the%20list%2C%20state%20leaders%20are%20waiting%20with%20trepidation%20the%20next%20list.%20They%20are%20unsure%20as%20to%20what%20winnability%20criteria%20were%20applied%20in%20candidate%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECongress%20is%20confident%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20centrally-guided%20election%20management%20in%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20Congress%20is%20holding%20wide%20consultations.%20All%20its%20state%20stalwarts%20have%20rallied%20behind%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate%2C%20Kamal%20Nath.%20In%20the%20candidate%20screening%20committee%20three%20important%20names%20%E2%80%93%20Suresh%20Pachouri%2C%20Arun%20Yadav%20and%20Ajay%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20were%20missing%20in%20the%20first%20list.%20On%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20bidding%2C%20they%20were%20included%20two%20days%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20none%20of%20the%20three%20publicly%20raised%20a%20voice%20against%20non-inclusion%20of%20their%20names%20earlier.%20Unlike%20in%20the%20past%20when%20the%20ticket%20selection%20process%20would%20trigger%20a%20howl%20of%20protests%20and%20relentless%20lobbying%20for%20tickets%2C%20the%20state%20Congress%20leaders%20this%20time%20around%20seem%20reconciled%20to%20bowing%20to%20the%20wishes%20of%20Kamal%20Nath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAICC%20general%20secretary%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20MP%20assembly%20election%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20is%20extending%20full%20cooperation%20to%20the%20PCC%20chief%2C%20who%20is%20much%20senior%20to%20him%20in%20the%20party.%20More%20significantly%2C%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20is%20wholeheartedly%20helping%20Kamal%20Nath%20in%20running%20the%20campaign%20like%20a%20tight%20ship.%20Both%20veterans%20have%20already%20finalised%20names%20of%20most%20of%20the%20230%20candidates%20to%20be%20fielded.%20Kamal%20Nath%20had%20tasked%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20with%20identifying%20suitable%20candidates%20for%20the%2066%20seats%20where%20the%20Congress%20has%20not%20won%20in%20the%20last%2030%20years.%20After%20completing%20a%20tour%20of%20those%20constituencies%20two%20months%20ago%2C%20Digvijaya%20submitted%20a%20list%20of%20probable%20candidates%20to%20Nath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENath%20had%20said%20he%20would%20announce%20candidates%20by%20August%20but%20decided%20against%20it%20on%20the%20high%20command%E2%80%99s%20directive.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20BJP%20came%20out%20with%20a%20list%20of%2039%20candidates%20and%20gloated%20over%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20do%20the%20same%20despite%20a%20public%20announcement.%20Congress%20sources%20say%20the%20list%20of%20all%20candidates%20is%20ready%20and%20awaiting%20a%20nod%20from%20party%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20before%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Scindia%20out%20of%20the%20party%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20never%20looked%20more%20united%20than%20it%20is%20today.%20Companionship%20between%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20is%20proving%20to%20be%20a%20great%20boost%20for%20the%20party%2C%20despite%20ideological%20differences%20between%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Hindutva%2C%20both%20differ%20so%20much%20that%20Nath%20sounds%20more%20like%20a%20BJP%20leader%20than%20Congress%20one.%20Digvijaya%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20%2C%20is%20fearless%20in%20articulating%20his%20secular%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20379px)%2085vw%2C%20379px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151458%2F367384106_900743161408994_2449008609315507060_n.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22379%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151458%2F367384106_900743161408994_2449008609315507060_n.jpeg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151458%2F367384106_900743161408994_2449008609315507060_n-200x300.jpeg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151458%2F367384106_900743161408994_2449008609315507060_n-683x1024.jpeg%20683w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671843%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22569%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20leader%20Kamal%20Nath.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FKamal%20Nath%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENath%20is%20pragmatic%20and%20ideology%20neutral.%20He%20is%20essentially%20an%20industrialist%20and%20his%20corporate%20style%20of%20politics%20does%20not%20brook%20rigidity%20of%20any%20kind.%20He%20loves%20to%20be%20called%20a%20Hanuman%20Bhakt%20and%20takes%20pride%20in%20having%20consecrated%20a%20100-foot%20tall%20idol%20of%20his%20favourite%20deity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20he%20played%20host%20to%20a%20controversial%20preacher%20Pradeep%20Mishra%20in%20his%20Chhindwara%20constituency%20with%20fanfare.%20Digvijaya%20had%20called%20the%20preacher%20a%20fraud%20in%20reaction%20to%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20call%20to%20Hindu%20women%20to%20arm%20themselves%20against%20%E2%80%9Clove%20jihad%E2%80%9C%20overtures%20from%20Muslim%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Nath%20is%20trying%20hard%20to%20poach%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20base%20of%20devout%20Hindus%2C%20Digvijaya%20is%20seeking%20to%20disabuse%20liberals%20and%20Muslims%20of%20misgivings%20these%20strong%20anti-BJP%20sections%20might%20harbour%20over%20the%20PCC%20president%E2%80%99s%20dalliance%20with%20Hindutva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20his%20political%20career%20has%20had%20more%20lows%20than%20highs%20since%20he%20led%20Congress%20to%20a%20crushing%20defeat%20in%20the%202003%20assembly%20election%2C%20Digvijaya%20has%20remained%20the%20most%20popular%20leader%20among%20liberals%20and%20Muslims%20owing%20to%20his%20unflinching%20commitment%20to%20secularism.%20Having%20regained%20the%20trust%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20during%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%2C%20Digvijaya%20has%20reemerged%20as%20the%20most%20powerful%20Congress%20leader%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20current%20powerful%20stature%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20campaigning%20for%20the%202018%20assembly%20election%2C%20when%20Digvijaya%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20take%20centrestage%20lest%20his%20presence%20reminded%20the%20people%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdark%20period%E2%80%9D%20when%20he%20was%20the%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Scindia%20factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20campaign%20for%20the%202018%20assembly%20election%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20that%20the%20BJP%20lost%20by%20a%20slender%20margin%2C%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20catchy%20slogan%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMaaf%20karo%20Maharaj%2C%20hamara%20neta%20Shivraj%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Forgive%20us%20King%2C%20our%20leader%20is%20Shivraj)%E2%80%99%2C%20implying%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20hope%20that%20the%20people%20in%20the%20state%20will%20continue%20to%20prefer%20the%20three-time%20chief%20minister%20over%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%2C%20who%20was%20widely%20speculated%20to%20be%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20March%202020%2C%20when%20Scindia%E2%80%99s%20revolt%20against%20the%20Congress%20helped%20the%20BJP%20snatch%20power%20from%20the%20Kamal%20Nath-led%20Congress%20government%2C%20the%20fourth-time-lucky%20chief%20minister%20and%20the%20Congress%20turncoat%20emerged%20as%20two%20parallel%20power%20centres%20in%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20coming%20assembly%20election%2C%20neither%20Shivraj%20nor%20the%20Maharaj%20is%20in%20the%20reckoning%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20post.%20They%20have%20been%20sidelined%20as%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20central%20leadership%20(read%20Shah)%20appears%20to%20consider%20both%20too%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20Congress%20onslaught%20to%20spearhead%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20Chouhan%20because%20of%20face-fatigue%20plaguing%20the%20longest%20serving%20BJP%20chief%20minister%20and%20Scindia%20because%20of%20the%20lurking%20fear%20of%20massive%20sabotage%20in%20the%20coming%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scion%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Gwalior%20state%20may%20have%20extracted%20his%20pound%20of%20flesh%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ministerial%20jobs%20for%20his%2011%20supporters%20in%20the%20Chouhan%20cabinet%2C%20besides%20adjustment%20of%20his%20nominees%20in%20the%20party%20set-up%20and%20various%20sinecures%20in%20return%20for%20propping%20up%20the%20BJP%20government%2C%20but%20the%20sudden%20transfer%20of%20political%20clout%20to%20Scindia%20and%20company%20has%20upset%20inner%20dynamics%20in%20the%20BJP%2C%20causing%20deep%20resentment%20in%20core%20party%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBarring%20a%20few%20outspoken%20ones%2C%20the%20disgruntled%20refrained%20from%20venting%20their%20ire%20against%20the%20growing%20political%20power%20of%20the%20Scindia%20acolytes%20at%20their%20expense%20for%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20lest%20their%20anger%20invite%20disciplinary%20action.%20They%20were%20acutely%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20party%20would%20not%20brook%20any%20action%20that%20might%20jeopardise%20the%20government%20running%20on%20the%20shoulders%20of%20the%20turncoats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20assembly%20election%20approaching%2C%20they%20feel%20emboldened%20enough%20to%20voice%20their%20pent-up%20furore.%20While%20the%20ordinary%20workers%20and%20lower%20rung%20BJP%20office%20bearers%20are%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20grumpy%20but%20silent%20as%20they%20await%20candidate%20nominations%20to%20decide%20their%20future%20course%20of%20action%2C%20many%20ticket%20hopefuls%20have%20already%20quit%20the%20party%2C%20citing%20no%20future%20in%20the%20BJP%20on%20account%20of%20Scindia%E2%80%99s%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151329%2F374191826_877937867035946_661087423820502970_n.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151329%2F374191826_877937867035946_661087423820502970_n.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07151329%2F374191826_877937867035946_661087423820502970_n-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671841%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBJP%20leaders%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%20(L)%2C%20J.P.%20Nadda%20(centre)%20and%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FShivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quitters%20are%20of%20two%20types%3A%20hardcore%20party%20leaders%20who%20see%20ticket%20denial%20coming%2C%20as%20their%20chosen%20seats%20are%20already%20held%20by%20Scindia%20supporters%2C%20and%20those%20who%20had%20followed%20the%20Union%20civil%20aviation%20minister%20to%20leave%20the%20Congress%20and%20join%20the%20BJP.%20All%20of%20them%20have%20joined%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHailing%20mostly%20from%20Scindia%E2%80%99s%20pocket%20borough%20in%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20region%2C%20the%20defectors%20said%20that%20they%20had%20made%20a%20mistake%20in%20aligning%20with%20the%20Maharaj.%20They%20are%20seeing%20a%20future%20in%20the%20Congress%20which%2C%20they%20claim%2C%20is%20all%20set%20to%20come%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20to%20jump%20the%20BJP%20ship%20is%20Virendra%20Raghuvanshi%2C%20a%20two-time%20MLA%20from%20Kolaras%20in%20Shivpuri%20in%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20region.%20While%20announcing%20his%20resignation%20on%20August%2031%2C%20he%20accused%20supporters%20of%20Scindia%20of%20corruption%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpersecution%20of%20original%20BJP%20workers%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20alleged%20that%20when%20he%20tried%20to%20raise%20the%20matter%20with%20Chouhan%2C%20he%20was%20silenced.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20Raguvanshi%20joined%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20Nath.%20Along%20with%20Raghuvanshi%2C%20former%20BJP%20MLA%20Bhanwar%20Singh%20Shekhawat%2C%20who%20had%20been%20vocal%20against%20Scindia%20for%20quite%20some%20time%2C%20also%20joined%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20series%20of%20desertions%20from%20the%20BJP%20began%20in%20May%20this%20year%2C%20with%20senior%20party%20leader%20and%20former%20minister%20Deepak%20Joshi%20joining%20the%20Congress.%20Joshi%2C%20son%20of%20former%20chief%20minister%20late%20Kailash%20Joshi%2C%20joined%20the%20party%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Nath%20at%20the%20Congress%20headquarters.%20Another%20former%20BJP%20legislator%2C%20Radhelal%20Baghel%2C%20also%20joined%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20May%2C%20over%20a%20dozen%20BJP%20leaders%20including%20former%20MLAs%20have%20switched%20sides.%20Plus%2C%20BJP%20workers%20in%20thousands%20have%20left%20the%20party%20for%20the%20Congress%20across%20the%20state%20in%20phases%20and%20batches%20over%20the%20last%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20political%20defection%20has%20been%2C%20mostly%2C%20one%20way%20so%20far%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20BJP%20to%20the%20Congress.%20Very%20few%20from%20the%20Congress%20have%20crossed%20over%20to%20the%20BJP.%20This%20is%20a%20reverse%20trend%3B%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20previous%20assembly%20elections%2C%20defections%20used%20to%20happen%20from%20the%20Congress%20to%20the%20BJP.%20The%20Scindia%20factor%20seems%20to%20have%20acted%20as%20a%20major%20catalyst%20in%20the%20reversal%20of%20the%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20worries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Scindia%20factor%2C%20however%2C%20is%20largely%20confined%20to%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20and%2C%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20Malwa%20regions.%20In%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20state%20such%20as%20Mahakoshal%2C%20Vindhya%20and%20Bundelkhand%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%20is%20facing%20the%20cadre%E2%80%99s%20ire%20due%20to%20perceived%20neglect%20of%20their%20respective%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahakoshal%20was%20without%20representation%20until%20last%20month%20when%20former%20minister%20Gauri%20Shankar%20Bisen%20was%20re-indicted%20in%20the%20cabinet.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20Vindhya%20region%20got%20its%20only%20minister%20with%20the%20induction%20of%20former%20minister%20Rajendra%20Shukla.%20From%20Bundelkhand%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20picked%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Uma%20Bharti%E2%80%99s%20nephew%20Rahul%20Lodhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20ministers%20have%20got%20only%20two%20months%20to%20enjoy%20their%20privileges%2C%20and%20the%20people%20in%20these%20regions%20see%20the%20cabinet%20expansion%20as%20tokenism%20that%20came%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20regional%20imbalance%20in%20the%20cabinet%20is%20a%20relatively%20minor%20reason%20for%20public%20anger.%20The%20overarching%20factor%20in%20the%20strong%20anti-incumbency%20against%20the%20chief%20minister%20is%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Will%20the%20BJP's%20Karnataka%20Loss%20Have%20an%20Impact%20on%20Elections%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwill-the-bjps-karnataka-loss-have-an-impact-on-elections-in-madhya-pradesh%5C%22%3EWill%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Karnataka%20Loss%20Have%20an%20Impact%20on%20Elections%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20pattern%20of%20its%20successful%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%9C40%25%20commission%20government%E2%80%9D%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20Congress%20is%20relentlessly%20cornering%20the%20Chouhan%20government%20and%20dubbing%20it%20%E2%80%9C50%25%20commission%20%3Cem%3Eki%20sarkar%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20slogan%20seems%20to%20be%20resonating%20with%20the%20electorate%20and%20it%20is%20showing%20in%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20desperation%20for%20diverting%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20attention%20from%20the%20Congress%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20resorted%20to%20announcing%20freebies%20to%20all%20sections%20with%20no%20regard%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20open%20and%20strong%20disapproval%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frevdi-culture-welfare-narendra-modi%5C%22%3Ewhat%20he%20called%20%E2%80%98revdi%20culture%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20More%20strikingly%2C%20Chouhan%20has%20copied%20promises%20from%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Vachan%20Patra%E2%80%99%20or%20manifesto%20relating%20to%20women%2C%20electricity%20consumers%20and%20farmers.%20Chouhan%20seems%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20the%20Congress%20promises%20had%20unseated%20the%20BJP%20in%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20scheme%20of%20things%20devised%20by%20the%20BJP%20high%20command%20for%20electioneering%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20that%20has%20played%20down%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20influence%2C%20his%20role%20appears%20to%20be%20confined%20to%20exploiting%20the%20resources%20at%20his%20command%20to%20the%20hilt.%20And%20he%20is%20sparing%20no%20efforts%20in%20this%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20a%20day%20has%20passed%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20when%20Chouhan%20has%20not%20announced%20one%20mega%20scheme%20or%20another%2C%20or%20bonanzas%20to%20woo%20different%20sections%20of%20voters.%20He%20seems%20to%20be%20banking%20most%20on%20the%20Ladli%20Behna%20Yojna%20which%20provides%20for%20Rs%201%2C000%20per%20woman%20per%20month%20to%20nearly%201.5%20crore%20potential%20beneficiaries%2C%20with%20the%20promise%20to%20hike%20it%20to%20Rs%203%2C000%20if%20the%20BJP%20is%20voted%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frakesh-dixit%5C%22%3ERakesh%20Dixit%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Bhopal-based%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694080238000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcentral-bjp-leadership-takes-control-of-madhya-pradesh-campaign-and-has-a-bumpy-road-ahead%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20state%20BJP%20has%20seen%20a%20slew%20of%20defections%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20with%20many%20leaders%20unhappy%20with%20the%20course%20the%20party%20has%20taken%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20Congress%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20looking%20more%20united%20than%20ever.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Howard%20Marks%20warns%20more%20companies%20will%20default%20as%20they%20feel%20the%20full%20force%20of%20the%20Fed's%20inflation%20fight%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224896%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Howard%20Marks%20of%20Oaktree%20in%20front%20of%20an%20Oaktree%20label%20on%20a%20white%20filing%20cabinet.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https