ger%20continue%20with%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners'%20programs%20after%20the%20March%202022%20Bitcoin%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20affect%20them%20so%20much%20that%20they%20would%20say%3A%20'Hang%20on%2C'%20or%20they%20would%20withdraw%20from%20applying%20because%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20they%20didn't%20have%20that%20liquidity%20anymore%2C%20or%20weren't%20comfortable%20with%20participating%20in%20one%20of%20these%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcryptocurrency-millionaires-new-wealth-digital-currency-henley-partners-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694078108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f991528a7840001961db7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcryptocurrency-millionaires-new-wealth-digital-currency-henley-partners-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%2088%2C000%20people%20have%20%241%20million%20or%20more%20in%20cryptocurrency%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20got%20their%20wealth%20through%20crypto%20trading%2C%20per%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40insider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcryptocurrency-millionaires-new-wealth-digital-currency-henley-partners-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Brace%20for%20stocks%20to%20crash%2025%25%20-%20and%20a%20recession%20to%20strike%20by%20spring%2C%20top%20economist%20David%20Rosenberg%20warns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221094%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20Rosenberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F644a76c9da6d7b0019bd6fff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22547%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDavid%20Rosenberg.%3Cp%3ECNBC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20recession%20will%20hit%20by%20the%20spring%2C%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20will%20crash%20by%2025%25%20or%20more%2C%20David%20Rosenberg%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmerican%20consumers%20have%20propped%20up%20the%20economy%20but%20they're%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20tapping%20out%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERising%20home%20prices%20aren't%20good%20news%20as%20they%20reflect%20weak%20demand%20meeting%20even%20weaker%20supply%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20will%20crater%20by%20spring%2C%20causing%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20to%20crash%20by%2025%25%20or%20more%2C%20David%20Rosenberg%20has%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20recession%20hasn't%20happened%20by%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DQyrgmBNcfSc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20WTFinance%20podcast%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20wipe%20the%20egg%20off%20my%20face%2C%20and%20I'll%20write%20a%20report%20saying%2C%20'I%20was%20wrong%2C%20the%20business%20cycle%20has%20been%20repealed%20after%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20hiked%20interest%20rates%20from%20nearly%20zero%20to%20north%20of%205%25%20since%20last%20spring%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20curb%20historic%20inflation.%20Short-term%20Treasuries%20are%20also%20paying%20larger%20yields%20than%20long-term%20government%20bonds%2C%20signaling%20Wall%20Street%20expects%20an%20economic%20downturn%20to%20spur%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20The%20economy%20has%20never%20gone%20through%20a%20Fed%20tightening%20cycle%20where%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Frecession-stock-market-crash-inverted-yield-curve-federal-reserve-powell-2023-6%5C%22%3Eyield%20curve%20was%20inverted%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20not%20suffered%20a%20recession%2C%20Rosenberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rosenberg%20Research%20president%20described%20the%20American%20consumer%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BEnergizer%20bunny%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20households%20have%20kept%20spending%20relentlessly%20for%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%20However%2C%20he%20warned%20their%20stimulus-juiced%20savings%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbond-king-bill-gross-consumer-spending-outlook-economy-fe-government-2023-7%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%20running%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20student-debt%20repayments%20resumed%20this%20month%2C%20and%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstephanie-pomboy-economy-stock-market-outlook-fed-pivot-rates-debt-2023-9%5C%22%3Emounting%20signs%20of%20consumer%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20rising%20delinquency%20on%20credit-card%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20batteries%20are%20going%20to%20run%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20consumer%20recession%20is%20inescapable%2C%20it's%20only%20going%20to%20be%20a%20question%20of%20how%20bad%2C%20not%20whether.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20chief%20North%20American%20economist%20at%20Merrill%20Lynch%20predicted%20unemployment%20would%20tick%20upward%20and%20wage%20growth%20would%20slow%20as%20the%20full%20impacts%20of%20the%20Fed's%20rate%20hikes%20are%20felt.%20The%20deteriorating%20economic%20picture%20isn't%20priced%20into%20assets%20currently%2C%20meaning%20investors%20could%20be%20in%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20rude%20surprise%26quot%3B%20within%20months%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20Rosenberg%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20stock%20market%20typically%20plunges%2030%25%20in%20a%20recession.%20He%20suggested%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20could%20drop%20by%20about%2025%25%20from%20its%20current%20level%20to%20around%203%2C400%20points%2C%20or%20roughly%2030%25%20from%20its%20peak%20of%20over%204%2C800%20points%20at%20the%20start%20of%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20also%20shrugged%20off%20the%20recent%20increase%20in%20home%20prices%20as%20evidence%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20depressed%26quot%3B%20housing%20market%2C%20not%20a%20healthy%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProspective%20buyers%20are%20balking%20at%20paying%20near-record%20prices%20and%20taking%20on%20mortgages%20when%20interest%20rates%20have%20more%20than%20doubled%20since%20the%20start%20of%20last%20year.%20Would-be%20sellers%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhome-prices-housing-market-forecast-mortgage-rates-corcoran-shark-tank-2023-8%5C%22%3Erefraining%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20listing%20their%20homes%2C%20as%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20up%20cheap%20mortgage%20rates%20they've%20locked%20in%2C%20and%20pay%20through%20the%20nose%20for%20their%20next%20place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20created%20a%20really%20sclerotic%20housing%20market%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-explained-mortgage-rates-fed-inventory-home-prices-house-2023-6%5C%22%3Every%20weird%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20prices%20have%20only%20climbed%20because%20supply%20has%20dropped%20even%20more%20than%20demand%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20economist%20also%20drew%20a%20parallel%20between%20the%20current%20market%2C%20where%20investors%20are%20assuming%20next%20year%20will%20be%20as%20rosy%20as%20this%20year%2C%20and%20the%20period%20before%20the%20housing%20bubble%20burst%20and%20triggered%20a%20global%20financial%20crisis%20in%20late%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnybody%20who%20was%20willing%20to%20superimpose%20or%20extrapolate%202007%20into%202008%20summarily%20got%20their%20heads%20chopped%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20might%20reli