%20to%20speak%20to%20multiple%20buyers%20at%20once%20to%20create%20FOMO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20can%20happen%20in%2090%20days.%20I%20lost%20my%20first%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fencyclopedia%2Facquisition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquisition%20offer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20got%20married%2C%20almost%20lost%20another%20offer%2C%20persuaded%20the%20buyer%20to%20stick%20with%20it%2C%20and%20finally%20sold%20my%20first%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20any%20moment%2C%20the%20right%20shove%20from%20the%20wrong%20direction%20might've%20killed%20my%20deal.%20Thankfully%20it%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20I%20now%20realize%20many%20of%20my%20acquisition%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fleadership%2F7-common-mistakes-first-time-entrepreneurs-make-and-how-to%2F435058%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emistakes%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20preventable.%20No%20acquisition%20is%20perfect%2C%20but%20preparing%20properly%20can%20help%20you%20avoid%20most%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20exit%20went%20smoother%20because%20I%20knew%20what%20to%20expect.%20I%20learned%20that%20lesson%20the%20hard%20way%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20don't%20have%20to.%20With%20my%20experience%20as%20a%20guide%2C%20I%20hope%20you%20can%20avoid%20these%20common%20acquisition%20mistakes%20and%20secure%20a%20better%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAre%20these%20lessons%20foolproof%3F%20No%2C%20but%20they%20can%20help%20you%20skirt%20preventable%20mistakes%20that%20might%20doom%20your%20acquisition%20before%20it%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Run%20due%20diligence%20on%20your%20own%20company%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20conduct%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fencyclopedia%2Fdue-diligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edue%20diligence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20your%20business%20to%20minimize%20risk.%20Due%20diligence%20goes%20through%20several%20phases%2C%20getting%20more%20rigorous%20as%20your%20deal%20matures.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20buyer%20might%20accept%20a%20P%26amp%3BL%20when%20making%20an%20offer%20but%20will%20ask%20for%20much%20more%20financial%20data%20in%20the%20closing%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20private%20equity%20firm%20that%20acquired%20my%20first%20startup%2C%20Bizness%20Apps%2C%20asked%20for%20dozens%20of%20spreadsheets%20during%20due%20diligence.%20It%20wanted%20data%20on%20everything%20from%20how%20often%20our%20biggest%20customers%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fgrowing-a-business%2Fhow-churn-destroys-businesses-and-how-to-stop-it-at-yours%2F329652%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echurned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20how%20many%20support%20tickets%20we%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20I%20tracked%20that%20data%20while%20building%20the%20company.%20If%20I'd%20had%20to%20scramble%20for%20it%20while%20closing%2C%20I%20might've%20appeared%20messy%20or%20disorganized%2C%20threatening%20my%20deal.%20Avoid%20this%20by%20running%20due%20diligence%20yourself%20so%20you're%20confident%20entering%20the%20process%20with%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20due%20diligence%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECollecting%20legal%2C%20HR%20and%20accounting%20documents%20into%20a%20single%20folder.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeriodically%20pulling%20numbers%20on%20revenue%2C%20churn%2C%20web%20traffic%20and%20more.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBuilding%20a%20confidential%20information%20memorandum%20(CIM)%20to%20market%20your%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20common%20due%20diligence%20questions%2C%20or%20ask%20buyers%20what%20they%20look%20for%20before%20closing%20a%20deal.%20Then%20collect%20answers%20and%20evidence%20inside%20a%20data%20room%20(a%20shareable%2C%20online%20repository%20like%20a%20Google%20Drive%20folder)%20for%20easy%20access%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Build%20early%20relationships%20with%20potential%20buyers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20sell%20Bizness%20Apps%20when%20I%20founded%20the%20company.%20Only%20two%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Ftopic%2Fexit-strategy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexit%20possibilities%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0existed%20back%20then%3A%20selling%20through%20my%20connections%20or%20a%20broker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20broker%20would%20market%20my%20startup%20and%20connect%20me%20with%20potential%20buyers%20in%20return%20for%20a%20cut%20of%20the%20purchase%20price.%20That%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20me%2C%20so%20I%20cultivated%20potential%20buyer%20relationships%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20shortlist%20consisted%20of%20people%20and%20companies%20we'd%20worked%20with%20and%20private%20equity%20firms%20I%20thought%20would%20be%20interested%20in%20my%20company's%20progress.%20Every%20quarter%2C%20I%20shared%20updates%20so%20they%20could%20watch%20our%20success.%20I%20reminded%20myself%20that%20everyone%20we%20worked%20or%20networked%20with%20could%20potentially%20acquire%20Bizness%20Apps%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDid%20it%20take%20more%20time%20and%20effort%20to%20keep%20those%20relationships%20going%3F%20Yes.%20But%20when%20it%20was%20time%20to%20exit%2C%20one%20of%20those%20private%20equity%20firms%20offered%20%2430%20million%20for%2070%20percent%20of%20the%20company.%20The%20deal%20ultimately%20fell%20through%2C%20but%20the%20offer%20probably%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20as%20high%20had%20I%20not%20fostered%20a%20relationship%20with%20that%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20working%20with%20other%20B2B%20businesses%2C%20suppliers%2C%20firms%20or%20entrepreneurs%2C%20consider%20them%20a%20ready-made%20buyer%20pool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Sell%20at%20the%20right%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20time%20to%20sell%20is%20when%20your%20business%20is%20doing%20well%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it's%20making%20money%2C%20growing%20fast%20and%20delighting%20your%20customers.%20You%20might%20want%20to%20chase%20more%20growth%20and%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fgrowing-a-business%2Fwhat-every-founder-needs-to-know-about-the-valuation-gap%2F442153%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20valuation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20disaster%20can%20strike%20at%20any%20moment%20%E2%80%94%20like%20when%20Apple%20changed%20its%20developer%20guidelines%20and%20almost%20put%20Bizness%20Apps%20out%20of%20business%20(we%20recovered%2C%20but%20you%20never%20know%20what's%20around%20the%20corner).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20expect%20buyers%20to%20get%20excited%20by%20falling%20revenue%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fgrowing-a-business%2F5-reasons-why-your-business-is-losing-customers%2F313463%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustomer%20losses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Show%20them%20your%20business's%20current%20and%20potential%20success%20by%20selling%20at%20a%20high%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETiming%20plays%20a%20big%20role%20personally%2C%20too.%20If%20you're%20overwhelmed%2C%20you%20can't%20commit%20to%20the%20selling%20process.%20Selling%20your%20business%20is%20not%20a%20casual%20task%20you%20can%20knock%20out%20on%20the%20weekend.%20You%20need%20time%20to%20plan%20and%20manage%20your%20acquisition%20to%20land%20the%20highest%20price%20and%20best%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20dropped%20everything%20to%20complete%20due%20diligence%20requests%20within%20minutes%20of%20the%20buyer%20emailing%20me.%20Even%20at%20my%20wedding%2C%20mid-deal%2C%20I%20sneaked%20away%20to%20respond%20to%20emails.%20I'm%20not%20saying%20you%20should%20be%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ethat%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0committed%2C%20but%20letting%20hours%2C%20days%20or%20weeks%20pass%20between%20messages%20will%20inevitably%20slow%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potentially%20kill%20%E2%80%94%20your%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Value%20your%20business%20reasonably%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFirst-time%20sellers%20(myself%20included)%20frequently%20overvalue%20their%20businesses.%20When%20I%20launched%20Bizness%20Apps%20in%20the%20late%202000s%2C%20I%20believed%20that%20all%20SaaS%20founders%20valued%20their%20businesses%20by%20multiplying%20their%20revenue%20by%2010.%20That's%20what%20I%20read%20in%20the%20news%20headlines%2C%20at%20least.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20reality%2C%20only%20the%20rapidly%20growing%20businesses%20with%20negative%20churn%20and%20high%20net%20revenue%20retention%20use%20those%20multiples.%20I%20soon%20learned%20that%20valuations%20are%20complex%20formulas%20dependent%20on%20several%20variables.%20Founders%20rarely%20close%20for%20the%20full%20amount%20they%20value%20their%20business%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETry%20to%20be%20realistic%20about%20your%20expectations.%20It's%20okay%20to%20leave%20room%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dentrepreneur.com%2Bnegotiation%26rlz%3D1C5CHFA_enUS949US950%26oq%3Dentrepreneur.com%2Bnegotiation%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIGCAEQRRhAMgYIAhBFGDvSAQgyMzQzajBqN6gCALACAA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20buyers%20won't%20entertain%20a%20number%20you%20can%20only%20back%20up%20with%20your%20emotions.%20You'll%20have%20to%20justify%20your%20asking%20price%20with%20data%20and%20evidence.%20And%20any%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fnews-and-trends%2Fmicromanagement-tops-workplace-red-flags-report%2F457491%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered%20flags%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0found%20during%20due%20diligence%20can%20ultimately%20hurt%20your%20valuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20valuation%20as%20a%20starting%20point%20for%20negotiations%2C%20and%20go%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Speak%20to%20multiple%20buyers%20at%20once%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20multiple%20buyers%20ensures%20you%20don't%20miss%20a%20great%20offer%20and%20gives%20you%20leverage%20with%20your%20frontrunner.%20A%20solo%20buyer%20can%20delay%20the%20deal%20and%20make%20ruthless%20demands.%20Instead%2C%20create%20urgency%20by%20involving%20multiple%20buyers%20to%20better%20your%20price%20or%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eif%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0your%20business%20sells%20but%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eto%20whom%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0you%20sell%20it.%20Let%20your%20buyer%20know%20they're%20one%20of%20several%20you're%20considering%20%E2%80%94%20create%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fliving%2F5-simple-ways-to-overcome-the-fear-of-missing-out%2F439188%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFOMO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you're%20only%20talking%20to%20one%20buyer%20at%20a%20time%2C%20they'll%20feel%20no%20urgency%20to%20strike%20a%20deal%2C%20and%20you'll%20start%20losing%20leverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20also%20consider%20listing%20on%20a%20startup%20acquisition%20marketplace%20like%20my%20company%2C%C2%A0Acquire.com%2C%20where%20you%20can%20connect%20with%20large%2C%20qualified%20buyer%20pools%20to%20generate%20buzz%20around%20your%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Conduct%20due%20diligence%20on%20the%20buyer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWho%20said%20due%20diligence%20was%20only%20for%20buyers%3F%20You're%20entrusting%20years%20of%20hard%20work%20and%20a%20team%20of%20faithful%20employees%20to%20the%20buyer.%20Are%20they%20equipped%20to%20handle%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20sold%20Bizness%20Apps%2C%20I%20called%20up%20the%20CEOs%20of%20the%20past%20ten%20companies%20my%20buyer%20acquired%20and%20asked%20them%20how%20the%20buyer%20approached%20the%20deal.%20Any%20issues%20during%20or%20after%20the%20acquisition%3F%20Did%20they%20re-negotiate%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20or%20push%20for%20onerous%20terms%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20confirming%20your%20buyer's%20legitimacy%20and%20ensuring%20you're%20entering%20a%20deal%20with%20someone%20you%20can%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fleadership%2F3-ways-to-build-trust-and-confidence-in-your-team%2F442240%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrust%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20Don't%20assume%20anything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20first-time%20founders%20entertain%20the%20notion%20that%20a%20company%20like%20Google%20will%20swoop%20in%20and%20offer%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20acquire%20their%20startup.%20We've%20seen%20it%20happen%20before.%20Facebook%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2Fvideos%2Fbusiness%2F2022%2F10%2F20%2Fsnapchat-facebook-buyout-offer-2013-vault-orig-ht.cnn-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffered%20%243%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20Snapchat.%20Adobe%20recently%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.adobe.com%2Fnews%2Fnews-details%2F2022%2FAdobe-to-Acquire-Figma%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0its%20%2420%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20Figma.%20But%20what%20are%20the%20chances%20of%20that%20happening%20for%20every%20founder%20with%20a%20brilliant%20product%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20assume%20any%20buyer%20will%20approach%20you%20with%20a%20wad%20of%20cash.%20Preparing%20for%20exit%20takes%20just%20that%20%E2%80%94%20preparation.%20You'll%20have%20to%20work%20hard%20to%20sell%20your%20startup%2C%20all%20while%20running%20your%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20leads%20to%20a%20second%20big%20assumption%3A%20Don't%20celebrate%20a%20done%20deal%20when%20you've%20only%20signed%20a%20letter%20of%20intent%20(LOI).%20The%20LOI%20is%20a%20non-binding%20agreement%20that%20kicks%20off%20negotiations.%20Wait%20to%20pop%20the%20Champagne%20until%20after%20the%20money%20lands%20in%20your%20bank%20account%20on%20closing%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E8.%20Constantly%20sell%20your%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20admit%20that%20I%20was%20a%20bit%20cocky%20when%20talking%20to%20early%20buyers%20in%20my%20first%20exit.%20I%20believed%20I%20had%20the%20best%20business%20to%20sell%2C%20and%20I%20led%20those%20conversations%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20are%20you%20buying%20or%20not%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20should%20have%20focused%20on%20what%20the%20buyer%20and%20I%20could%20achieve%20together%20with%20the%20deal%2C%20wooing%20them%20to%20work%20with%20me%20towards%20an%20outcome%20that%20made%20us%20both%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20aren't%20just%20looking%20at%20your%20startup.%20They're%20evaluating%20countless%20other%20acquisitions%20and%20won't%20hesitate%20to%20drop%20you%20if%20a%20better%20opportunity%20appears.%20Remind%20them%20about%20the%20support%20you'll%20offer%20post-acquisition%2C%20the%20great%20team%20they'll%20inherit%20and%20the%20opportunities%20for%20growth%20in%20the%20future.%20Do%20everything%20you%20can%2C%20at%20all%20times%2C%20to%20de-risk%20this%20acquisition%20for%20the%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20remember%20that%20acquisitions%20are%20relationship%20transactions%2C%20not%20just%20financial%20ones.%20The%20more%20you%20connect%20with%20your%20buyers%20personally%2C%20the%20more%20they'll%20cooperate%20with%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E9.%20Don't%20get%20greedy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20tell%20you%20how%20many%20times%20I've%20watched%20sellers%20turn%20down%20amazing%20offers%20hoping%20a%20better%20one%20comes%20along.%20Nine%20times%20out%20of%20ten%2C%20that%20seller%20doesn't%20get%20another%20offer%2C%20let%20alone%20one%20with%20a%20better%20price%20or%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20you%20have%20to%20say%20yes%2C%20especially%20when%20an%20offer%20checks%20most%20or%20all%20of%20your%20boxes.%20Wait%20too%20long%2C%20and%20your%20revenue%20could%20dip.%20Slumps%20won't%20help%20you%20attract%20a%20higher%20offer%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20turned%20down%20a%20few%20good%20deals%20before%20the%20private%20equity%20firm%20approached%20me%20with%20its%20offer%3A%20all%20cash%20at%20closing%2C%20a%20short%20transition%20period%20and%20more.%20I%20could've%20told%20the%20firm%20to%20wait%20so%20I%20could%20speak%20to%20more%20buyers%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22follow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fmoney-finance%2Fan-entrepreneurs-guide-to-startup-pricing-strategies%2F428342%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrive%20up%20the%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20just%20didn't%20make%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20offered%20everything%20I%20wanted%20for%20a%20good%20price%20and%20from%20a%20reputable%20buyer.%20If%20I%20waited%20too%20long%2C%20I%20feared%20the%20buyer%20would%20reduce%20the%20price%2C%20add%20terms%20I%20didn't%20want%20(like%20an%20earnout)%20or%20rescind%20the%20offer%20completely.%20So%20I%20took%20the%20risk%20and%20struck%20a%20deal.%20I%20have%20no%20regrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E10.%20Keep%20your%20composure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20nerves%20will%20be%20taut%20as%20a%20piano%20wire%20the%20nearer%20you%20get%20to%20closing.%20Sure%2C%20everything's%20going%20smoothly%20now%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20isn't%20done%20until%20the%20money%20lands%20in%20your%20account.%20Unexpected%20circumstances%20or%20last-minute%20due%20diligence%20issues%20can%20give%20the%20buyer%20cold%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeeks%20before%20closing%20the%20Bizness%20Apps%20deal%2C%20the%20buyer%20said%20we%20had%20too%20many%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dentrepreneur.com%2Bsupport%2Btickets%26rlz%3D1C5CHFA_enUS949US950%26oq%3Dentrepreneur.com%2Bsupport%2Btickets%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIGCAEQIxgnMgYIAhAjGCcyCAgDEAAYFhgeMggIBBAAGBYYHjIICAUQABgWGB4yCAgGEAAYFhgeMggIBxAAGBYYHjIICAgQABgWGB4yCggJEAAYhgMYigXSAQgyMTc0ajBqN6gCALACAA%26so