ver%2C%20helped%20her%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F282454%2Fmother-son-duo-leenas-how-to-grow-mushroom-farm-earnings-success%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpand%20the%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20move%20towards%20a%20good%20yield%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20year%2C%20Nidhi%20used%20her%20ancestral%20house%20of%201%2C500%20sq%20ft%20to%20set%20up%20a%20lab%20with%20dedicated%20rooms%20for%20incubation%2C%20inoculation%2C%20and%20pasteurisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20decided%20to%20grow%20mushroom%20spawns%20on%20her%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20she%20grows%20the%20spawns%2C%20Nidhi%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20we%20boil%20wheat%20and%20barley%20straws.%20Then%20we%20sterilise%20them%20with%20fungicides.%20We%20then%20pack%20them%20into%20small%20packets%20and%20add%20them%20into%20autoclaves%20for%20sterilisation.%20After%20incubation%20using%20the%20mother%20spawn%2C%20we%20store%20the%20packets%20for%20six%20to%20seven%20days.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20a%20white-coloured%20fungus%20gets%20layered%20over%20the%20wheat%20grain.%20That%20is%20how%20spawns%20are%20prepared.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENidhi%20also%20highlights%20the%20mistakes%20farmers%20should%20avoid%20while%20preparing%20mushroom%20spawns.%20She%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CUsually%2C%20farmers%20take%20shortcuts%20in%20preparing%20spawns.%20For%20instance%2C%20spawns%20should%20be%20soaked%20overnight%20in%20fungicide%20and%20kept%20aside%20overnight.%20They%20skip%20these%20steps%20to%20take%20a%20shortcut%20and%20keep%20it%20only%20for%20two%20to%20three%20hours.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20might%20not%20observe%20the%20damage%20then%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20visible%20after%2010-15%20days%20when%20a%20fungus%20attacks%20their%20produce%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C